UID:8139-1775296800-1775311200@hardtruth.com
SUMMARY:Easter Bourbon Hunt
DESCRIPTION:Why should kids have all the fun?\n\n\nJoin us for the ultimate grown-up Easter adventure: the Easter Bourbon Hunt! We’re hiding eggs stuffed with boozy surprises\, tasting vouchers\, and maybe even a golden egg with a prize worth hopping for. \nSip as you search — because nothing says spring fever like hunting eggs with a cocktail in hand. \n\n\nFrom bold bourbons to crisp craft beers and creative spirits\, this hunt is all about flavor\, fun\, and a little friendly competition.\nGrab your crew\, bring your thirst\, and let’s get cracking—because this isn’t your grandma’s Easter egg hunt!21+\nNo cancellations
URL:https://hardtruth.com/event/easter-bourbon-hunt-4/
CATEGORIES:Featured
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Hard Truth Distilling Co.
X-SOURCE-URL:https://hardtruth.com/events/ (Nashville, IN - 16 mi)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Halifax:20260405T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Halifax:20260405T150000
DTSTAMP:20260330T230919
CREATED:20260105T185146Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260309T131657Z
UID:8141-1775383200-1775401200@hardtruth.com
SUMMARY:Easter Brunch
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Easter at Hard Truth Distilling Co. with a relaxed\, open‑seating brunch experience in the House of Rye. Gather with family and friends and enjoy the rustic charm\, wooded surroundings\, and signature Hard Truth hospitality that make events here unforgettable.Pair your meal with handcrafted cocktails or sips from the mimosa bar\, then enjoy a stroll through the distillery grounds as you continue your Easter celebration. \nBrunch buffet includes:\nGlazed ham carving station\nLamb chops\nMini quiches\nHam & cheese croissant\nSpring pea salad\nDinner rolls\nChef’s choice vegetables\nRoasted Potatoes\nPasta salad\nAssorted desserts\nIced tea\, lemonade\, and water \nHandcrafted cocktails and mimosa bar will be available for additional purchase. \nBuffet is all ages; must be 21+ to purchase and consume alcohol. \nSeating is limited\, so make your reservation today.
URL:https://hardtruth.com/event/easter-brunch-2/
CATEGORIES:Featured
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Hard Truth Distilling Co.
X-SOURCE-URL:https://hardtruth.com/events/ (Nashville, IN - 16 mi)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Halifax:20260410T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Halifax:20260410T203000
DTSTAMP:20260330T230919
CREATED:20260304T134524Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260324T181038Z
UID:8263-1775844000-1775853000@hardtruth.com
SUMMARY:An Evening With Fred Minnick
DESCRIPTION:Some nights are easy to come by. Others—you feel them before they even begin. This is one of those nights.  \n\n\n  \n\n\nJoin us at Hard Truth Distilling Co. for an evening with Fred Minnick—a voice that’s helped shape how America understands whiskey\, one honest story at a time. As part of his national tour for Bottom Shelf: How a Forgotten Brand of Bourbon Saved One Man’s Life\, Fred brings his story to a place that lives and breathes the craft every day.  \n\n\n  \n\n\nThis won’t feel like a talk—it’ll feel like pulling up a chair and settling in. Over chef-curated appetizers and thoughtfully crafted cocktails\, Fred will share stories from Bottom Shelf\, including a live reading\, along with reflections on bourbon’s deeper roots—where it comes from\, and why it still matters.  \n\n\n  \n\n\nThere’s a weight to Fred’s words. Not because they’re loud—but because they’re true. And on this night\, that truth meets the spirit of Hard Truth—where whiskey\, story\, and community come together in a way you don’t often find.  \n\n\n  \n\n\nThe evening closes with a book signing and a chance to meet Fred—so you don’t just hear the story\, you carry it with you.  \n\n\n  \n\n\nWhat’s Included  \n\n\n\nA copy of Bottom Shelf by Fred Minnick \nChef-curated appetizers \nSpecialty-developed cocktails (or alcohol-free pairings) \nA live reading and intimate conversation with Fred Minnick \nBook signing and meet-and-greet \n\n\n\n  \n\n\nTicket Options  \n\n\n\n\n\n$90 – Full experience with cocktails \n\n\n\n\n$65 – Alcohol-free experience \n\n\n\n  \n\n\nIf you know bourbon\, you know Fred. If you don’t—this is where the story starts.  \n\n\n  \n\n\nSeats are limited. Come early. Stay late. Discover the Truth. 
URL:https://hardtruth.com/event/an-evening-with-fred-minnick/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Hard Truth Distilling Co.
